/home/archon/FormalizationProjects/Algebraic-Jacobian-Challenge/blueprint/src/chapters/AbelJacobi.tex-The three results above are formalised through the Albanese framework of Chapter~\ref{chap:Jacobian}. In the absence of Mathlib's Pic-scheme machinery, the Jacobian is defined (Layer~I) as the underlying scheme of an Albanese witness uniform in the marked point (Theorem~\ref{thm:nonempty_jacobianWitness}); the universal-property data $(\iota_P,\, \text{factorisation})$ is then carried by the Albanese predicate (Definition~\ref{def:IsAlbanese}) and projects directly into the three results of this chapter (Layer~II): the Abel--Jacobi map $\alpha_P := \iota_P$ of Definition~\ref{def:ofCurve}, its pointed property of Lemma~\ref{lem:comp_ofCurve}, and the universal factorisation of Theorem~\ref{thm:exists_unique_ofCurve_comp}. Existence of a uniform-over-$P$ Albanese object is the single remaining mathematical hypothesis pending the formalisation of either Pic-scheme representability (Route~A), symmetric-power quotients plus Stein factorisation (Route~B), or rigidity for $C \to A$ established \emph{directly over $k$} (genus-$0$ sub-case, via \cref{thm:rigidity_over_kbar} per the iter-127 over-k commitment; no base-change to $\bar k$ and no Galois descent of morphism equality enter, and sub-step C.2.f of \S~C.2 is correspondingly DROPPED).
